## Application Boot Flow

### Step-by-Step Boot Process

```
1. Browser loads index.html
   ↓
2. Vite dev server injects main.jsx as entry point
   ↓
3. main.jsx executes:
   ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(<App />)
   ↓
4. App.jsx initializes:
   ├── Reads darkMode from localStorage
   ├── Creates Material-UI theme (light/dark mode)
   ├── Wraps with AuthProvider (provides auth context to entire app)
   ├── Wraps with ThemeProvider (provides MUI theme to entire app)
   ├── Wraps with BrowserRouter (enables React Router)
   ├── Renders <AppRoutes />
   ↓
5. AppRoutes.jsx initializes:
   ├── Creates layout: Sidebar + Navbar + Page content
   ├── Defines all routes (<Routes>)
   ├── On first load, redirects "/" to "/dashboard"
   ↓
6. If not logged in:
   ├── ProtectedRoute checks AuthContext.token
   ├── If no token, redirects to "/login"
   ├── Shows Login page
   ↓
7. If logged in:
   ├── AuthContext has token & user from localStorage
   ├── ProtectedRoute allows access to page
   ├── Page mounts and fetches data from API
   ├── Displays content to user
```

### Detailed Boot Code Flow

**index.html:**
```html
<div id="root"></div>
<script type="module" src="/src/main.jsx"></script>
```

**main.jsx:**
```javascript
ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root')).render(
  <React.StrictMode>
    <App />
  </React.StrictMode>
)
```

**App.jsx:**
```javascript
function App() {
  // 1. Initialize theme from localStorage
  const [darkMode, setDarkMode] = useState(() => {
    const saved = localStorage.getItem("darkMode");
    return saved ? JSON.parse(saved) : false;
  });

  // 2. Create MUI theme based on darkMode
  const theme = createTheme({
    palette: {
      mode: darkMode ? "dark" : "light",
      // ... color definitions
    }
  });

  // 3. Return component tree with providers
  return (
    <BrowserRouter>
      <AuthProvider>
        <ThemeProvider theme={theme}>
          <CssBaseline />
          <ToastContainer />
          <AppRoutes />
        </ThemeProvider>
      </AuthProvider>
    </BrowserRouter>
  );
}
```

