## Authentication Flow

### Overview
This app uses **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)** for authentication. Tokens are stored in `localStorage` and automatically attached to all API requests.

### Authentication Flow Diagram

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    AUTHENTICATION FLOW                           │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

STEP 1: USER NAVIGATES TO APP
    ↓
AuthContext checks localStorage for saved token
    ├── IF token exists:
    │   ├── Restore token and user from localStorage
    │   ├── Set AuthContext state
    │   └── User is "logged in"
    │
    └── IF no token:
        └── User state is null

STEP 2: USER NOT LOGGED IN → SHOWS LOGIN PAGE
    ↓
User enters credentials (email, password)
    ↓
Login form submits via ProductService.login()
    ├── Axios POST to /auth/login
    ├── Backend validates credentials
    ├── Backend returns { token, user, ... }
    ↓
AuthService.login() stores in localStorage:
    ├── localStorage.setItem("token", token)
    ├── localStorage.setItem("user", JSON.stringify(user))
    ├── AuthContext.setToken(token)
    └── AuthContext.setUser(user)
    ↓
React Router navigates to /dashboard
    ↓
ProtectedRoute checks AuthContext.token
    ├── Token exists → Allows access
    └── Renders Dashboard

STEP 3: AUTHENTICATED REQUESTS
    ↓
When any component calls API:
    ├── axios.js request interceptor runs
    ├── Gets token from localStorage
    ├── Adds header: Authorization: Bearer <token>
    ├── Sends request to backend
    ↓
Backend validates token
    ├── IF valid:
    │   └── Processes request normally
    │
    └── IF expired/invalid:
        └── Returns 401 Unauthorized
            ├── Frontend intercepts (response interceptor)
            ├── Shows error message to user
            └── (Can optionally redirect to login)

STEP 4: USER LOGOUT
    ↓
User clicks Logout (in Navbar or Sidebar)
    ↓
AuthService.logout() clears everything:
    ├── localStorage.removeItem("token")
    ├── localStorage.removeItem("user")
    ├── AuthContext.setToken(null)
    ├── AuthContext.setUser(null)
    ↓
React Router navigates to /login
    ↓
User sees login page again
```

### AuthContext Code

**Context/AuthContext.jsx:**
```javascript
export const AuthContext = createContext();

export const AuthProvider = ({ children }) => {
  // Initialize from localStorage on mount
  const [token, setToken] = useState(localStorage.getItem("token"));
  const [user, setUser] = useState(
    JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("user"))
  );

  // Provides login method
  const login = (token, user) => {
    localStorage.setItem("token", token);
    localStorage.setItem("user", JSON.stringify(user));
    setToken(token);
    setUser(user);
  };

  // Provides logout method
  const logout = () => {
    localStorage.removeItem("token");
    localStorage.removeItem("user");
    setToken(null);
    setUser(null);
  };

  return (
    <AuthContext.Provider value={{ token, user, login, logout }}>
      {children}
    </AuthContext.Provider>
  );
};
```

### useAuth Custom Hook

**services/AuthService.js:**
```javascript
export const useAuth = () => {
  const context = useContext(AuthContext);
  
  const { token, user, login, logout } = context;
  
  return {
    isLoggedIn: !!token,        // Boolean: is user logged in?
    token,                       // JWT token string
    user,                        // User object { id, email, name, ... }
    login,                       // Function to set token & user
    logout,                      // Function to clear token & user
  };
};
```

