## State Management & Context

### Context API Usage

The app uses **React Context API** for global state management. Currently using:

1. **AuthContext** - Authentication state (token, user)
2. **ThemeContext** (optional) - Theme mode (light/dark)

### State Management Hierarchy

```
Global State (Context)
├── AuthContext
│   ├── token (string or null)
│   ├── user (object or null)
│   ├── login() function
│   └── logout() function
│
└── ThemeContext (in App.jsx)
    ├── darkMode (boolean)
    └── setDarkMode() function

Local Component State (useState)
├── ProductList: products[], searchTerm, filters
├── AddProduct: formValues, formErrors
├── Dashboard: stats, chartData
├── UserList: users[], selectedUser
└── ... (each component manages its own data)
```

### Example: Accessing Auth Context

```javascript
import { useAuth } from "../services/AuthService";

function Navbar() {
  const { isLoggedIn, user, logout } = useAuth();
  
  if (!isLoggedIn) return null;
  
  return (
    <nav>
      <p>Welcome, {user.name}</p>
      <button onClick={logout}>Logout</button>
    </nav>
  );
}
```

