## Route Structure

### Routes Defined in AppRoutes.jsx

```
/                    → Redirects to /dashboard

PUBLIC ROUTES:
/login               → Login page (anyone can access)
/register            → Register page (anyone can access)

PROTECTED ROUTES (require authentication):
/dashboard           → Dashboard with stats & charts
/products            → Product listing page
/products/add        → Add new product form
/products/edit/:id   → Edit product form (id = product ID)
/users               → User management (admin only)
/reports             → Analytics & reports
/settings            → User settings
```

### How Route Protection Works

```javascript
// In AppRoutes.jsx
<Route
  path="/products"
  element={
    <ProtectedRoute>
      <ProductList />
    </ProtectedRoute>
  }
/>

// In ProtectedRoute.jsx
const ProtectedRoute = ({ children }) => {
  const { token } = useContext(AuthContext);
  
  if (!token) {
    return <Navigate to="/login" replace />;
  }
  
  return children;  // Render the protected component
};
```

### Route Navigation Flow

```
User enters URL or clicks link
    ↓
React Router matches route
    ↓
IF route is protected:
    ├── <ProtectedRoute> checks AuthContext.token
    ├── IF token exists:
    │   └── Renders component
    └── IF no token:
        └── Redirects to /login
        
IF route is public:
    └── Renders component directly
```

