    ↓
ProductService calls:
    api.post("/products", productData)
    ↓
REQUEST:
    axios.js REQUEST INTERCEPTOR:
        Gets token from localStorage
        Adds Authorization header
        ↓
    BACKEND receives:
        POST /api/products
        Headers: { Authorization: Bearer <token> }
        Body: { name, price, quantity, manufacturer }
        ↓
    BACKEND processes:
        Validates token
        Saves product to database
        Returns: { id, name, price, ... }

RESPONSE:
    axios.js RESPONSE INTERCEPTOR:
        Processes successful response
        ↓
    AddProduct.jsx receives new product
        ↓
    Shows success toast: "Product added successfully!"
        ↓
    Navigates to /products
        ↓
    ProductList.jsx mounts
        ↓
    Fetches all products (with new product included)
        ↓
    Displays updated list to user
```

### Example 3: User Navigation & State Preservation

```
SCENARIO: User is on /products, navigates to /dashboard, then back to /products

USER NAVIGATES TO /DASHBOARD:
User clicks "Dashboard" in Sidebar
    ↓
React Router changes URL to /dashboard
    ↓
AppRoutes.jsx updates <Routes> to render Dashboard
    ↓
Dashboard component mounts
    ↓
useEffect fetches dashboard data
    ↓
Dashboard renders with new data

PRODUCTS COMPONENT STATE:
