### api/axios.js - HTTP Client with Interceptors

**Purpose**: Configure HTTP client with authentication and error handling.

```javascript
import axios from "axios";

// Create Axios instance with default configuration
const api = axios.create({
  baseURL: "http://localhost:8088/api",  // Backend base URL
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",   // Send/receive JSON
  },
  timeout: 10000,                        // 10 second timeout for requests
});

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// REQUEST INTERCEPTOR: Runs BEFORE every API request
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
api.interceptors.request.use(
  (config) => {
    // 1. Get JWT token from localStorage
    const token = localStorage.getItem("token");
    
    // 2. If token exists, add it to request headers
    if (token) {
      config.headers["Authorization"] = `Bearer ${token}`;
      // Header format: "Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>"
    }
    
    // 3. Return modified config
    return config;
  },
  // If request setup fails, reject the promise
  (error) => Promise.reject(error)
);

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// RESPONSE INTERCEPTOR: Runs AFTER every API response
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
api.interceptors.response.use(
  // Success case: response status 2xx
  (response) => {
    // Just pass through successful responses
    return response;
  },
  // Error case: response status 4xx, 5xx or network error
  (error) => {
    // Check if it's a network connectivity error
    if (error.code === 'ERR_NETWORK' || error.message === 'Network Error') {
      console.error('🔴 BACKEND NOT REACHABLE!');
      console.error('Make sure Spring Boot backend is running on http://localhost:8088');
      error.message = 'Backend server is not running. Please start Spring Boot application.';
    }
    
    // Reject error so component's try-catch block can handle it
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
);

export default api;
```

**How Interceptors Work**:

```
HTTP Request Flow:
  ↓
REQUEST INTERCEPTOR
  ├── Read token from localStorage
  ├── Add Authorization header: "Bearer <token>"
  └── Pass modified request to backend
  ↓
BACKEND PROCESSES REQUEST
  ├── Validate JWT token
  ├── Process request
  └── Send response back
  ↓
RESPONSE INTERCEPTOR
  ├── Check if response successful (2xx status)
  ├── Check if network error occurred
  ├── Modify error message if needed
  └── Pass response to component
  ↓
COMPONENT RECEIVES RESPONSE
  ├── In try block: data is processed
  └── In catch block: error is handled
```

