## Frontend Process Explanation (Complete Flow)

### Complete User Journey: From Page Load to App Ready

This section explains EVERYTHING that happens from the moment a user opens the app until they see the dashboard.

#### Step 1: Browser Loads Application

```
User types: http://localhost:3000 in browser
  ↓
Browser loads index.html from Vite dev server
  ↓
HTML Response:
  <html>
    <body>
      <div id="root"></div>
      <script type="module" src="/src/main.jsx"></script>
    </body>
  </html>
  ↓
Vite injects React and JSX compiler
```

#### Step 2: React App Initializes

```
main.jsx executes:
  ↓
ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root'))
  ├── Gets the <div id="root"> from HTML
  └── Creates React root render target
  ↓
.render(<App />)
  ├── Renders App component into the div
  └── App component begins initialization
```

#### Step 3: App.jsx Loads Providers

```
App() function executes:
  ↓
[PROVIDER 1] BrowserRouter initializes
  ├── Sets up React Router
  └── Watches for URL changes
  ↓
[PROVIDER 2] AuthProvider initializes
  ├── Creates AuthContext
  ├── Checks localStorage for "token"
  ├── Checks localStorage for "user"
  ├── Sets initial state:
  │   ├── token = localStorage.getItem("token") or null
  │   └── user = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("user")) or null
  ├── Provides {token, user, login, logout} to entire app
  └── If token exists → User was previously logged in
  ↓
[PROVIDER 3] ThemeProvider initializes
  ├── Checks localStorage for "darkMode"
  ├── Creates Material-UI theme object
  ├── Applies colors based on dark/light mode
  └── Provides theme to all MUI components
  ↓
Returns JSX with <AppRoutes />
```

#### Step 4: Route Matching & Decision

```
AppRoutes component renders:
  ↓
React Router checks current URL path
  ├── If path is /login or /register → public page
  └── If path is anything else → protected page
  ↓
Check authentication status:
  ├── Does AuthContext.token exist?
  │
  ├── IF YES (User logged in):
  │   ├── Render layout: Sidebar + Navbar + Page
  │   ├── Render page component (Dashboard, Products, etc.)
  │   └── Page fetches data from API
  │
  └── IF NO (User not logged in):
      ├── <ProtectedRoute> checks token
      ├── Token is null/undefined
      └── Redirect to /login with <Navigate to="/login" replace />
```

#### Step 5A: User NOT Logged In → Show Login Page

```
AuthContext.token is null
  ↓
ProtectedRoute redirects to /login
  ↓
React Router renders <Login /> component
  ↓
Login component renders:
  ├── Email input field
  ├── Password input field
  └── Login button
  ↓
User sees login form
```

#### Step 5B: User Logged In → Show Dashboard

```
AuthContext.token exists
  ↓
ProtectedRoute allows access
  ↓
React Router renders layout:
  ├── <Sidebar /> with navigation menu
  ├── <Navbar /> with user profile dropdown
  └── <Dashboard /> (or other page)
  ↓
Layout renders on screen
  ↓
Dashboard.jsx useEffect() runs:
  ├── Makes API calls to fetch data
  ├── Axios request interceptor adds JWT header
  ├── Backend validates token
  ├── Backend returns data
  └── Dashboard renders data
  ↓
User sees dashboard with stats and charts
```

