### Error Handling Throughout Frontend

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│      ERROR HANDLING FLOW                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

SCENARIO 1: NETWORK ERROR (Backend Not Running)
──────────────────────────────────────────────
User clicks to load products
  ↓
ProductService.getAllProducts() called
  ↓
api.get("/products") sent to http://localhost:8088/api/products
  ↓
NO SERVER LISTENING ON PORT 8088
  ↓
Axios catches network error:
error.code = "ERR_NETWORK"
  ↓
Response interceptor runs:
if (error.code === 'ERR_NETWORK') {
  error.message = 'Backend server is not running'
}
  ↓
Component's catch block:
catch (error) {
  toast.error(error.message)
  console.error('Backend not reachable')
}
  ↓
User sees toast: "Backend server is not running"
Page shows spinner or empty state

SCENARIO 2: UNAUTHORIZED ERROR (Invalid Token)
──────────────────────────────────────────────
User has old/expired token in localStorage
  ↓
Component makes API call
  ↓
Axios adds Authorization header: "Bearer <old_token>"
  ↓
Backend validates token
  ↓
Token is expired or invalid
  ↓
Backend returns: 401 Unauthorized
  ↓
Component's catch block:
catch (error) {
  if (error.response?.status === 401) {
    // Could redirect to login
    navigate("/login")
  }
  toast.error("Session expired. Please login again")
}
  ↓
User redirected to login page

SCENARIO 3: VALIDATION ERROR (Bad Data)
────────────────────────────────────────
User submits AddProduct form with:
- Name: "" (empty)
- Price: "abc" (not a number)
  ↓
Formik validation runs BEFORE submit:
validationSchema: Yup.object({
  name: Yup.string().required("Name is required"),
  price: Yup.number().required("Price is required"),
})
  ↓
Validation fails
  ↓
Error messages display under each field:
- "Name is required"
- "Price must be a number"
  ↓
Submit button remains disabled
  ↓
User cannot submit until errors fixed

SCENARIO 4: SERVER VALIDATION ERROR (Backend Rejects)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
User submits form with valid Formik validation
Product name: "Laptop" (already exists in database)
  ↓
Form submits:
const newProduct = await ProductService.addProduct({name: "Laptop", ...})
  ↓
Axios adds token and sends to backend
  ↓
Backend receives and validates:
if (productExists(name)) {
  return 409 Conflict
  message: "Product with this name already exists"
}
  ↓
Component's catch block:
catch (error) {
  const message = error.response?.data?.message
  // "Product with this name already exists"
  
  toast.error(message)
}
  ↓
User sees: "Product with this name already exists"
  ↓
User can fix and re-submit form
```

