## React Hooks Used Throughout App

### useState - Manage Local Component State

```javascript
// Basic syntax:
const [state, setState] = useState(initialValue)

// Examples:
const [products, setProducts] = useState([])           // Start with empty array
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)           // Start with false
const [user, setUser] = useState({name: "", email: ""}) // Start with object

// Updating state:
setProducts([...oldProducts, newProduct])  // Add item to array
setLoading(true)                           // Change boolean
setUser({...user, name: "John"})          // Update object property
```

### useEffect - Run Code After Render

```javascript
// Syntax:
useEffect(() => {
  // Code runs after component renders
  return () => {
    // Cleanup code (optional)
  }
}, [dependencies])

// Examples:

// Run once on mount (fetch data)
useEffect(() => {
  fetchProducts()
}, [])

// Run when data changes (update when id changes)
useEffect(() => {
  fetchProduct(productId)
}, [productId])

// Run every render (watch all changes)
useEffect(() => {
  saveToLocalStorage()
})

// Cleanup example
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setTimeout(() => {
    toast.close()
  }, 3000)
  
  return () => clearTimeout(timer)  // Clean up on unmount
}, [])
```

### useContext - Access Global State

```javascript
// Access AuthContext anywhere:
const { token, user, login, logout } = useContext(AuthContext)

// Access ThemeContext:
const { darkMode, setDarkMode } = useContext(ThemeContext)

// Custom hook that wraps useContext:
const useAuth = () => {
  const context = useContext(AuthContext)
  return context
}
```

