## Component Lifecycle Understanding

### Component Mount → Update → Unmount

```
MOUNT PHASE (Component First Creates)
──────────────────────────────────────
1. React creates component
2. useState() initializes state
3. Component renders JSX
4. useEffect() with [] runs (data fetching)
5. Component appears on screen
6. User can interact

UPDATE PHASE (State or Props Change)
──────────────────────────────────────
1. setState() called or prop changes
2. React re-renders component
3. New JSX returns from component
4. Browser updates DOM
5. useEffect() with dependencies runs
6. Component displays new content

UNMOUNT PHASE (Component Removed)
──────────────────────────────────
1. Component is removed from DOM
2. useEffect() cleanup runs
3. State is destroyed
4. Memory freed
```

