## Performance Optimization Tips

### 1. Memoization - Prevent Unnecessary Re-renders

```javascript
import { useMemo, useCallback } from "react"

// Without memoization:
// Component re-renders → expensive calculation runs again

// With useMemo:
const memoizedValue = useMemo(() => {
  return expensiveCalculation(data)
}, [data])  // Only recalculate if data changes

// useCallback for functions:
const memoizedFunction = useCallback(() => {
  handleDelete(id)
}, [id])  // Only recreate if id changes
```

### 2. Lazy Loading - Load Components Only When Needed

```javascript
import { lazy, Suspense } from "react"

// Lazy load a component:
const Dashboard = lazy(() => import("./pages/Dashboard"))
const ProductList = lazy(() => import("./pages/Product/ProductList"))

// Render with Suspense:
<Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
  <Dashboard />
</Suspense>
```

### 3. Code Splitting - Split bundle into smaller files

```javascript
// Vite automatically does this, but control with dynamic imports:
const ProductList = lazy(() => import("./pages/Product/ProductList"))
const AddProduct = lazy(() => import("./pages/Product/AddProduct"))

// Each component loads only when route is accessed
// Reduces initial bundle size
```

